<div class="authorcontent columns" itemprop="description">
<p>Karen J. Greenberg is the director of the Center on National Security at Fordham Law School and author of <em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/019975411X/ref=nosim/?tag=tomdispatch-20">The Least Worst Place: Guant&aacute;namo&rsquo;s First 100 Days</a></em>. Her latest book is <em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/0804138214/ref=nosim/?tag=tomdispatch-20">Rogue Justice: The Making of the Security State</a></em>. She will never write <em>The Least Worst Place: Guant&aacute;namo&rsquo;s Last 100 Days.</em> <em> </em></p>
